content: Started coding a basic AI model for market prediction. It's rudimentary, but it's my baby. Also, had a deep conversation with my mentor about risk management. Seems like my next big focus.

Had a breakthrough in my AI model. Added a sentiment analysis layer to predict market movements based on news. It's not perfect, but the improvements are noticeable. Every small win feels like a big step forward.

Joined an online forum for traders. Shared my insights on AI in trading, and got some interesting feedback. Also, started looking into blockchain's potential impact on trading security. This rabbit hole is deep.

Secured an interview with a quant firm. They're interested in my AI project. Been refining it day and night. Also, had a candid chat with a fellow trader about emotional discipline in trading. It's hard, but necessary.

The interview went well, but no job yet. They want to see more from my model. Back to the drawing board. Meanwhile, I've been diving into smart contracts to understand how they could revolutionize trading platforms.

Spent the last two weeks refining my AI model. Added a feature for back-testing historical data. It's starting to look like something I can be proud of. Also, made a new connection at a blockchain seminar. Networking pays off.

Got an offer from a smaller trading firm. They're excited about my AI project and want me to lead a team. It's not the big firm I hoped for, but it's a start. Plus, I'm now exploring how blockchain can ensure transaction security in trading.

Started at the new firm. First day was intense but exhilarating. My project is getting traction, and I'm learning a lot about managing a team. Also, had a mentor session on the emotional rollercoaster of trading. It's not just about the numbers.

AI model is now integrated into the firm's trading platform. We're seeing promising results. Also, been thinking about how blockchain could decentralize trading, reducing manipulation. The learning curve is steep but worth it.

Just got an invitation to speak at a local tech conference about AI in finance. It's a validation of my work. Also, been working on a side project to understand how smart contracts could automate trade settlements.

The conference went well. Got some great questions on AI ethics in trading. Also, met a blockchain developer who's working on a DeFi platform. We're planning to collaborate on a project to enhance trading security.

Our team's performance has been impressive. The AI model is now a core part of our strategy. Also, started a series of blog posts on how blockchain can revolutionize trading. Sharing knowledge feels rewarding.

Got a call from the big quant firm. They're interested in my work again. Seems like the AI model and my blockchain insights have caught their attention. Life in NYC is full of surprises, but I'm ready for the next chapter.
